

I generally setup two versions of NEURON one for testing with a GUI
and the other with MPI linked in.

unpack nrn and iv then jump into iv


mkdir -p ~/src/neuron
cd ~/src/neuron
tar zxvf ../iv-17.tar.gz
mv iv-17 iv
cd iv
./configure --prefix=`pwd` && make && make install

cd ..
tar zxvf nrn-X.X.tar.gz
mv nrn-X.X nrn
cd nrn

# now make your separate builds
mkdir gui
cd gui
../configure --prefix=`pwd` --with-iv=$HOME/neuron/iv --without-pvm
make && make install
cd ..
mkdir mpi
../configure --prefix=`pwd` --without-iv --with-paranrn
make && make install


In the working directory containing NMOL *.mod files, setup two
linkable libraries against the two nrn builds.

See the Makefile for instrstructions to make either the gui or mpi
version, otherwise use "make all"

$ make gui

or 

$ make mpi

To run a script in gui mode:

./guispecial par_golgi_test.hoc -
or 
./gui/special par_golgi_test.hoc -


The MPI version should be run in the background from the mpispecial
script or in batch mode.  "np" is the number of processors requested
(e.g. 1 to 50)

./mpispecial np par_batch.hoc > /tmp/batch.log 2>&1 &
